"20:51:4" : {s: 20, a: 51, w: 4, r: "قرن", t: "ٱلْقُرُونِ", l: "قَرْن", lc: 23, tl: "l-qurūni", lb: "যুগ",e: "(of) the generations", b: "প্রজন্ম, উম্মত", f: 7, rm: "to join one thing with another, couple. qarnin/qarnan - generation, century. qarn (dual qarnani, oblique qaraini, plu. qurun) - horn, trumpet. Often used to symbolise strength/power/glory. qarunun (pl. qurana) - mate, comrade, intimate companion. muqarranin - bound together. muqrinina - capable of subduing. muqtarinin - those formed in serried ranks, accompanying ones."},
